# Copy to .env (optional). Root .gitignore ignores .env — do not commit secrets.

# --- Local testing (default)
# If you open the app at http://localhost:5173 or http://127.0.0.1:5173, src/config/api.ts
# automatically uses http://localhost:5000 for the API. You do not need VITE_API_URL.

# If you open the dev server by machine IP (e.g. phone on same Wi‑Fi), set the API to your PC:
# VITE_API_URL=http://192.168.x.x:5000
# (Without this, non-localhost hosts default to the deployed API — correct for Vercel/production.)

# --- Production / staging (Amplify or CI)
# Set VITE_API_URL in the hosting provider’s environment before build, e.g.:
# VITE_API_URL=https://YOUR_API_ID.execute-api.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com/dev
